 <title>The colors behind TVs and Printers</title>
 <link>http://assorted.in/technology/the-colors-behind-tvs-and-printers</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;Some time ago, I wondered about this question...&lt;br /&gt;
Is there a reason why RGB (Red Green Blue) is used to create pictures in television and CMYK (Cyan Magenta Yellow and Key[black]) is used in printers? Can we use RGB in printers?&lt;br /&gt;
Corollary question - What color paint do we get if we mix red paint and green paint?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After some investigation, I compiled a detailed answer, which follows...&lt;br /&gt;
There are 2 kinds of objects that we percieve, differentiating by the method by which they manipulate light. There are sources and there are reflectors.&lt;/p&gt;
